[+++ b/spring-boot-docs/src/main/asciidoc/howto.adoc, +[[howto-disable-registration-of-a-servlet-or-filter]], +=== Disable registration of a Servlet or Filter, +As <<howto-add-a-servlet-filter-or-servletcontextlistener,described above>> any `Servlet`, +or `Filter` beans will be registered with the servlet container automatically. To disable, +registration of a particular `Filter` or `Servlet` bean create a registration bean for it, +and mark it as disabled. For example:, +, +[source,java,indent=0,subs="verbatim,quotes,attributes"], +----, +	Bean, +	public FilterRegistrationBean registration(MyFilter filter) {, +		FilterRegistrationBean registration = new FilterRegistrationBean(filter);, +		registration.setEnabled(false);, +		return registration;, +	}, +----, +, +, +]